# System Context Diagram (C4 Level 1)

> CrewCircle — Australian Workforce Management Platform
> View: System Context (highest level)
> Render with: Mermaid.js or any C4-compatible tool

```mermaid
C4Context
    title System Context Diagram — CrewCircle

    Person(employee, "Employee", "Clocks in/out, views roster, receives notifications")
    Person(manager, "Manager", "Creates rosters, manages team, reviews timesheets")
    Person(owner, "Business Owner", "Manages billing, views reports, configures settings")

    Enterprise_Boundary(crewcircle, "CrewCircle") {
        System(web_app, "Web Application", "Next.js 16 app for roster management, timesheets, and team admin", "Next.js + React")
        System(mobile_app, "Mobile Application", "React Native app for GPS time clock and roster viewing", "React Native + Expo")
        SystemDb(database, "PostgreSQL Database", "Stores users, rosters, timesheets, and billing data", "NeonDB")
        System_Ext(clerk, "Authentication Service", "User authentication, session management, OAuth", "Clerk")
        System_Ext(stripe, "Payment Processing", "Subscription billing, invoicing, webhook events", "Stripe")
    }

    Rel(employee, mobile_app, "Clocks in/out via", "HTTPS")
    Rel(employee, web_app, "Views roster via", "HTTPS")
    Rel(manager, web_app, "Manages rosters & team via", "HTTPS")
    Rel(owner, web_app, "Configures & pays via", "HTTPS")

    Rel(web_app, database, "Reads/writes data", "PostgreSQL Protocol")
    Rel(mobile_app, database, "Reads/writes data", "PostgreSQL Protocol")
    Rel(web_app, clerk, "Authenticates users via", "OAuth/HTTPS")
    Rel(mobile_app, clerk, "Authenticates users via", "OAuth/HTTPS")
    Rel(web_app, stripe, "Processes payments via", "HTTPS + Webhooks")

    UpdateRelStyle(employee, mobile_app, $offsetY="-30")
    UpdateRelStyle(employee, web_app, $offsetY="-10")
    UpdateRelStyle(manager, web_app, $offsetX="20")
    UpdateRelStyle(owner, web_app, $offsetX="40")
```

## Actors

| Actor | Description | Primary Touchpoint |
|-------|-------------|-------------------|
| Employee | Non-admin staff member | Mobile app (time clock), Web (roster view) |
| Manager | Shift planner & team lead | Web app (roster creation, team management) |
| Business Owner | Account administrator | Web app (billing, reports, settings) |

## Systems

| System | Technology | Responsibility |
|--------|-----------|----------------|
| Web Application | Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript | Roster management, timesheets, team admin, billing portal |
| Mobile Application | React Native, Expo | GPS time clock, roster viewing, push notifications |
| PostgreSQL Database | NeonDB (Serverless) | Persistent storage for all business data |
| Authentication | Clerk | User identity, sessions, OAuth providers |
| Payment Processing | Stripe | Subscription billing, invoicing, payment webhooks |

## Data Flow Summary

1. **Authentication:** User → Clerk → Web/Mobile App (JWT token)
2. **Roster Management:** Manager → Web App → Database
3. **Time Tracking:** Employee → Mobile App (GPS) → Database
4. **Billing:** Web App → Stripe (charge) → Webhook → Database (update subscription)
5. **Notifications:** Roster publish → Web App → Employee notification (email/push)

## Compliance Notes

- All data stored in **AWS ap-southeast-2** (Sydney, Australia)
- Australian Privacy Principles (APP) compliance required
- GST-inclusive pricing for all Australian customers
